=== Etymology ===
From {{OF.}} ''[[comete]]'' (French: ''[[comète]]''), from {{L.}} ''[[cometa]]'', from {{AG.}} [[κομήτης]] (''kometes'') "longhaired", referring to the tail of a comet, from [[κόμη]] (''kome'') "hair".

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

#A [[celestial body]] consisting mainly of [[ice]], [[dust]] and [[gas]] in an (usually very [[eccentric]]) [[orbit]] around the [[Sun]] and having a "tail" of melted matter blown back from it by the [[solar wind]] as it approaches the Sun.

